- Ordering: Events must be processed in the order they are given. If processing of an event ultimately fails (after retries), subsequent events should not be processed (to avoid out-of-order partial application).
- Audit trail correctness: _apply_log must accurately reflect applied adjustments (apply_delta calls) in order. We must not double-record the same adjustment as a result of retries.
- Idempotency / safety across retries: Re-running processing for the same event (immediately, as part of retries) must not double-apply an already-applied adjustment.

