Instead I return a read-only view of the internal dict using types.MappingProxyType. MappingProxyType prevents callers from mutating the returned mapping while still reflecting all future changes to the underlying dict. This preserves the original semantics while making external mutation impossible.

Readers of the shared state (the functions that read from _handlers) and confirmation they still work:
- get_handler(name): unchanged, returns the registered function object (works as before).
